        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Washington&#44; D. C.<lb/>
                May 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1876.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
            Philadelphia.<lb/>
            Dr. Sir&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>The bearers of this&#44; mess.<lb/> Goldstein and Rich&#44; visit your<lb/> city with the earnest endeavor<lb/> of enlisting the sympathies of our<lb/> Jewish fellow citizens to assist<lb/> in the payment of the build&#45;<lb/>ing of a &#34;Schule&#34;&#45;&#45;now nearly<lb/> completed&#8212;which will be a<lb/> credit to the Capitol of the nation<lb/> and of the Jews Everywhere.<lb/></p>
            <p>The Congregation is <hi rend="underline">strictly</hi><lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>orthodox.<lb/></p>
            <p>Knowing you sympathize with<lb/> such a meritorious movement&#44;<lb/> I take the liberty to request<lb/> that you will render these<lb/> gentlemen such assistance<lb/> as will be likely to subserve<lb/> the End in view.<lb/></p>
            <p>With great respect&#44;<lb/> I have the honor to be<lb/></p>
            <p>yours very truly<lb/>
            A. I. Solomons<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
